OL,6,FA statement from a friend of Mr Wilson
OL,7,Fhighlighted how he was diagnosed with
OL,8,Fcancer and lived alone.
OL,10,FThey said: "It was very cruel to watch
OL,11,Fa man who would do no harm to anybody
OL,12,Fagonise over losing so much money to a
OL,13,Ffraud."
OL,15,FMr Wilson, who also suffered from the
OL,16,Fearly stages of dementia, would wait
OL,17,Fby the phone in hope that McGinlay
OL,18,Fwould phone and pay back the money.
