OL,6,FThe second count of fraud relates to a
OL,7,Fcouple who were scammed out of #1,200
OL,8,Fafter McGinlay promised to carry out
OL,9,Fwork on their driveway in June 2022.
OL,11,FMcGinlay taunted the couple as they
OL,12,Fchallenged him on his fraud, accusing
OL,13,Fthe male of having dementia. He denied
OL,14,Fowing them money, stating: "Take me to
OL,15,Fcourt. I will wink at you."
OL,17,FMcGinlay, formerly of Carlisle, was
OL,18,Fsaid to have had issues with alcohol
OL,19,Fand gambling at the time.
